
SpineSeg
version 2.0 (June 2011)

SpineSeg is a medical analysis tool for semi-automatic segmentation of 
the spinal cord from magnetic resonance images, developed by
Felipe Bergo at the Dept. of Neurology, UNICAMP, Brazil.

Usage directions can be found in the PDF guide available at

http://www.liv.ic.unicamp.br/~bergo/spineseg

To compile SpineSeg you will need:

* The GCC compiler.
* The GTK+ 2.4.x libraries, or any later compatible version.
* The bzip2 library.

To compile, use

./configure
make

To install, do

make install (as root)

